HSBC Holdings plc Reiterates Buy Rating for Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSB)

Alonzo Mancillas |
Domingo, Julio 23, 2017







The Royal Dutch Shell Plc (LON:RDSB) Given a GBX 2560 Price Target at Morgan Stanley
The stock increased 0.54% or $0.29 during the last trading session, reaching $54.34. Toronto-Dominion Bank (NYSE:TD) has risen 8.67% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending.Royal Dutch Shell Plc (LON:RDSA) has received an average recommendation of "Buy" from the fifteen analysts that are now covering the stock, MarketBeat.com reports. Investors of record on Thursday, May 18th were issued a dividend of $0.47 per share. After $0.82 actual EPS reported by Royal Dutch Shell plc (ADR) for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -8.54 % negative EPS growth. About 637,383 shares traded. Royal Dutch Shell has GBX 2850 highest and GBX 1570 lowest target. It has underperformed by 3.92% the S&P500. One analyst has rated the stock with a sell rating, three have assigned a hold rating and fifteen have issued a buy rating to the company's stock. Therefore 50% are positive. The legal version of this piece of content can be viewed at https://transcriptdaily.com/2017/07/22/royal-dutch-shell-plc-rdsb-receives-consensus-rating-of-buy-from-brokerages-updated-updated-updated.html. The rating was downgraded by Citigroup on Wednesday, April 19 to "Sell". Jefferies has "Buy" rating and $66.70 target. The firm has "Outperform" rating given on Tuesday, December 15 by Credit Agricole.
The Royal Dutch Shell plc explores for natural gas and crude oil around the world, both in conventional fields and from sources, such as tight rock, shale and coal formations. The company's market capitalization is GBX 170.15 billion. The Company's segments include Integrated Gas, Upstream, Downstream and Corporate. It has a 29.08 P/E ratio. The Integrated Gas segment is engaged in the liquefaction and transportation of gas and the conversion of natural gas to liquids to provide fuels and other products, as well as projects with an integrated activity, ranging from producing to commercializing gas. UBS AG set a GBX 2,500 ($32.65) price objective on shares of Royal Dutch Shell Plc and gave the stock a "buy" rating in a report on Monday, March 6th. Royal Dutch Shell had 142 analyst reports since July 31, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Jefferies maintained the stock with "Buy" rating in Friday, June 23 report. The company was upgraded on Wednesday, October 14 by Argus Research. The stock of Royal Dutch Shell plc (ADR) (NYSE:RDS.A) has "Hold" rating given on Wednesday, August 5 by TheStreet. The firm earned "Buy" rating on Tuesday, February 16 by Bank of America. HSBC Holdings plc reaffirmed a buy rating and set a GBX 2,700 ($35.26) price target on shares of Royal Dutch Shell Plc in a research note on Thursday, April 13th. The rating was maintained by Societe Generale on Wednesday, November 2 with "Buy".Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with MarketBeat.com's FREE daily email newsletter.




