Product details




Share this page:











































 Please find below the full details of the product you clicked a link to view.









 RISK MANAGEMENT @ ROYAL DUTCH SHELL PLC 
 






 Case 
 
-

 Reference no. 111-072-1 
 







Authors:

D Satish; Manish Agarwal





Published by:

 IBS Case Development Center 
 (2011)
 
 



Length:
15 pages










Data source:
Published sources



Topics:

Risk management; Financial risk management; Royal Dutch Shell Plc; Financial risks; Other risk; Market risk; Credit risk; Foreign exchange risk; Management of interest rate risk; Management of price risk; Management of liquidity risk; Health, safety, security and environmental risk




Abstract:

 The case study provides a fundamental understanding of the different kinds of risks and their management. The case explains the risks facing the largest oil company of the world - Royal Dutch Shell Plc. The case further explains the management of each risk faced by the company. The case will help the students: 1) To demonstrate the understanding of the nature of various risks and alternative tools available for managing them; 2) To explain the various risks faced by Shell and the limitations of risk management; 3) To analyze the various costs involved in effective risk management. The case is meant for MBA / MS level students as part of a financial risk management / risk management curriculum. 
 




Settings:

Netherlands, Europe, Oil and gas



Related:








 RISK MANAGEMENT @ ROYAL DUTCH SHELL PLC 
 






 Teaching note 
 
-

 Reference no. 111-072-8 
 




















 No reviews
 




